# Tech Stack & API Guide: Albert AI Agent

This guide lists the specific tools, APIs, and infrastructure components that power **Albert**, the AI Sales Agent. Use this to understand the underlying ecosystem or for technical onboarding.

---

## 1. External APIs (Third-Party Services)

| API Name | Provider | Purpose in Albert |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Bird (Channels v2)** | Bird | Gateway for WhatsApp messaging. Handles sending/receiving messages and contact management. |
| **OpenRouter** | OpenRouter | Unified API for LLMs. Albert uses **GPT-4o** and **GPT-4o-mini** via this provider. |
| **Whisper API** | OpenAI | High-accuracy Speech-to-Text. Transcribes incoming WhatsApp voice notes into text. |
| **Calendly Webhook**| Calendly | Triggers Albert when a meeting is booked so he can automatically confirm it via WhatsApp. |
| **Supabase (REST)** | Supabase | Interface for the PostgreSQL database where lead data and chat logs are persisted. |
| **Helicone** | Helicone | Observability layer for LLM calls. used for cost tracking, caching, and debugging AI responses. |

---

## 2. Core Software Stack (The Engine)

| Component | Technology | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Web Framework** | **FastAPI** | A modern, high-performance Python framework used to build Albert's backend. |
| **Async Client** | **HTTPX** | Used for all outgoing API calls (to Bird, OpenAI, etc.) to ensure high concurrency. |
| **Pydantic** | **Pydantic v2** | Handles data validation and configuration management (settings). |
| **ORM/Client** | **Supabase-py** | Specific Python library used to interact with the Supabase/PostgreSQL backend. |

---

## 3. Data & Memory Layer

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Database** | **PostgreSQL** | Relational database (hosted on Supabase) for long-term storage of leads and messages. |
| **Cache/Memory** | **Redis** | In-memory store used for session tracking, message buffering, and state management. |

---

## 4. Infrastructure & DevOps

| Tool | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Railway** | Cloud platform used for hosting the web server and managing environment variables. |
| **GitHub** | Source code repository and driver for the CI/CD pipeline (auto-deploy to Railway). |
| **n8n** | (Optional) Automation platform used to trigger initial outreach messages from marketing forms. |

---

## 5. Interaction Workflow
1.  **Incoming Message**: Bird API sends a Webhook to Albert’s FastAPI server.
2.  **Buffering**: Redis stores the message for 3 seconds to see if more chaims follow.
3.  **Processing**: Albert retrieves the conversation history from Redis/Supabase.
4.  **AI Response**: LLM (via OpenRouter) generates a response based on the System Prompt.
5.  **Outgoing Message**: Albert shows a "Typing" indicator and sends the reply via Bird API in chunks.
6.  **Persistence**: The message is logged in Supabase for future reference.
